1
00:00:01,854 --> 00:00:05,564
Maharaj, you're always describing such a deep topics,

2
00:00:05,663 --> 00:00:08,273
and it can be deeper and deeper,

3
00:00:08,397 --> 00:00:14,257
and you've also just told us, you can start from Guru Maharaj's conception

4
00:00:14,769 --> 00:00:17,219
and go from there, and it is also very deep,

5
00:00:17,658 --> 00:00:22,618
and just now you've mentioned that mind cannot understand all of this stuff,

6
00:00:23,006 --> 00:00:27,726
but also we feel that we need some foundation like firm basics,

7
00:00:28,447 --> 00:00:30,427
especially newcomers.

8
00:00:30,674 --> 00:00:34,394
So, is it the proper approach that you just dive deep into those deep conceptions?

9
00:00:34,437 --> 00:00:38,557
No, what I've just said, your heart is hankering for something.

10
00:00:39,646 --> 00:00:42,206
Your heart is hankering. Who can fulfil that?

11
00:00:43,609 --> 00:00:45,279
That's foundational.

12
00:00:47,345 --> 00:00:49,885
Who can address what you heart is seeking?

13
00:00:51,840 --> 00:00:54,050
A person, place or thing in this world.

14
00:00:57,582 --> 00:01:01,582
You're searching for beauty. Krishna is Beauty personified.

15
00:01:04,239 --> 00:01:06,259
That is simple and direct.

16
00:01:07,466 --> 00:01:11,086
You're searching for happiness. Krishna is Happiness personified.

17
00:01:11,620 --> 00:01:14,160
Oh, how? Want to understand more?

18
00:01:14,552 --> 00:01:20,082
So, people are not searching for something superficial actually.

19
00:01:21,934 --> 00:01:26,324
By default they are, but that will not make them happy.

20
00:01:28,121 --> 00:01:30,051
Searching for superficial things.

21
00:01:31,250 --> 00:01:34,060
You know, the husk is not the rice.

22
00:01:34,748 --> 00:01:37,898
The shell is absent the substance.

23
00:01:40,531 --> 00:01:42,181
These are foundational things.

24
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:52,130
To understand that you're the spiritually conscious being

25
00:01:52,257 --> 00:01:56,227
in a body generated by karmic circumstance

26
00:01:56,263 --> 00:01:58,793
and you're searching for fulfilment.

27
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:02,407
That's foundational.

28
00:02:04,092 --> 00:02:05,892
So what will fulfil you?

29
00:02:06,904 --> 00:02:11,914
Any amount of the mundane or quality of mundane or

30
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:19,890
on account of your subjective nature must it be something located in the subjective world.

31
00:02:21,905 --> 00:02:25,905
I'm not here to hammer over somebody's head day after day:

32
00:02:26,081 --> 00:02:30,891
"You are not the body. You are the soul. Read the second chapter of Bhagavad Gita."

33
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:36,708
Sometimes. But I'm not going to speak every day this theme.

34
00:02:37,706 --> 00:02:40,316
I did that. For 10 years.

35
00:02:41,149 --> 00:02:46,109
So 10 years of hammering this on people's heads.

36
00:02:47,638 --> 00:02:51,668
You look in the Chaitanya Charitamrita and see how much of that type of hammering is there.

37
00:02:52,505 --> 00:02:54,345
So we are devotees of Mahaprabhu.

38
00:02:56,311 --> 00:02:59,691
So you can't just... We are discussing Mahaprabhu and talking about him. And you say:

39
00:02:59,701 --> 00:03:05,841
"It's all too high! You know, people just need to know what are they gonna do tomorrow morning when they wake up."

40
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:11,330
Oh, alright. But then we have to go all the way back to that.

41
00:03:12,157 --> 00:03:14,337
"These things are so high!" and then we go back.

42
00:03:14,385 --> 00:03:17,665
Can the infinite make itself known to the finite?

43
00:03:20,548 --> 00:03:22,018
Do you accept this principle?

44
00:03:22,030 --> 00:03:25,060
The infinite can make itself known to the finite.

45
00:03:25,646 --> 00:03:27,576
And someone says: "No, I don't accept that."

46
00:03:28,570 --> 00:03:30,070
And someone says: "Yes, I accept that."

47
00:03:30,070 --> 00:03:33,320
Right. Then we need to accept the principle of Revealed Truth.

48
00:03:33,922 --> 00:03:38,472
Here's this one level of Revealed Truth: in the Bible or the Quran or the Torah.

49
00:03:38,523 --> 00:03:42,873
Then another level of Revealed Truth: in the Vedas, the Upanishads, the Puranas.

50
00:03:42,987 --> 00:03:46,117
Another level of Revealed Truth: in the Mahapurana, the Bhagavatam.

51
00:03:46,138 --> 00:03:48,578
How serious are you to know these things?

52
00:03:52,782 --> 00:03:56,662
Or just always wanna go back to ABC?

53
00:03:57,445 --> 00:03:59,235
2 + 2 = 4

54
00:04:00,057 --> 00:04:03,207
We need addition, subtraction, you know...

55
00:04:03,831 --> 00:04:07,831
Gonna go back to grade one and go "ABCD", learn the ABCs.

56
00:04:08,361 --> 00:04:09,901
How does the song go?

57
00:04:11,594 --> 00:04:12,974
No, I know, how it goes.

58
00:04:17,027 --> 00:04:21,107
So it has the place, but [we] can't stay forever.

59
00:04:23,049 --> 00:04:27,119
And say: "Wow, grade three, they're discussing things that..." Yes.

60
00:04:27,997 --> 00:04:31,887
You're dealing with the Ultimate Reality and say: "Well, it's pretty deep!"

61
00:04:31,945 --> 00:04:34,395
I guess it should be, shouldn't it?

62
00:04:35,801 --> 00:04:39,801
It's the Ultimate Reality. From which everything has come.

63
00:04:40,155 --> 00:04:47,175
So, how much... How earnest, serious is someone to become acquainted with these things?

64
00:04:50,842 --> 00:04:52,242
And we're saying: "Yes, so then..."

65
00:04:52,254 --> 00:04:57,574
Read the Bhagavad Gita, read the second chapter of Bhagavad Gita about ātmajnāna,

66
00:04:57,584 --> 00:05:04,274
understand the difference between the body, the gross body, the subtle body, etc.

67
00:05:04,285 --> 00:05:05,635
That's general.

68
00:05:06,277 --> 00:05:07,627
Aham Brahmasmi ─

69
00:05:08,411 --> 00:05:13,211
that's not, in this sense, a Vaishnava aphorism.

70
00:05:13,358 --> 00:05:15,848
That's for everyone.

71
00:05:16,819 --> 00:05:19,069
"I am Spirit."

72
00:05:19,369 --> 00:05:22,759
The mayavadis say that, the vaishavas say, everyone says that.

73
00:05:24,420 --> 00:05:25,660
That's general.

74
00:05:27,605 --> 00:05:29,775
And someone says: "No, I don't accept that."

75
00:05:29,836 --> 00:05:31,706
Then they're not gonna go very far.

76
00:05:35,629 --> 00:05:38,049
And it's a waste of time to argue with them.

77
00:05:39,125 --> 00:05:43,625
They say: "No, i don't believe in God or Spirit." Okay. That's your choice.

78
00:05:44,772 --> 00:05:49,452
For those who do, there is a way to systematically study these things.

79
00:05:50,252 --> 00:05:53,272
We are primarily Gaudia-vaishnavas.

80
00:05:54,124 --> 00:05:58,234
That means we study the teachings of Sri Chaitanya Mahaprabhu.

81
00:06:00,207 --> 00:06:04,087
His teachings about Krishna-bhakti, devotion to Krishna.

82
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:10,540
So, that's our primary emphasis.

83
00:06:14,016 --> 00:06:17,346
But we understand, in another context, someone...

84
00:06:17,427 --> 00:06:19,607
they need, they want to...

85
00:06:20,371 --> 00:06:24,401
What would be appropriate for them is to hear ātmajnāna ─

86
00:06:25,274 --> 00:06:30,574
the analogy about the soul, the spirit ─ it's in the second chapter of Bhagavad Gita and other places.

87
00:06:32,428 --> 00:06:35,968
We believe that, we preach it all the time.

88
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:41,070
But here, I mean, the context of answering questions about Mahaprabhu,

89
00:06:42,830 --> 00:06:45,010
that would be to go backwards.

90
00:06:49,948 --> 00:06:56,108
Talking about the differences between Mahaprabhu's, you know, Puri pastimes and His Nabadwip pastimes.

91
00:06:58,483 --> 00:07:01,473
So, the question by its nature is a deep one.

92
00:07:01,838 --> 00:07:05,828
Then there must be some understanding about what is Nabadwip, what is Puri,

93
00:07:06,011 --> 00:07:10,941
who is Chaitanya Mahaprabhu, what is Vrindavan, Krishna, Jagannath, Dvaraka.

94
00:07:11,186 --> 00:07:12,646
All of these things.

95
00:07:13,978 --> 00:07:18,118
Which are the heart of the matter of the discussion of Gaudiya-vaishnavas,

96
00:07:19,272 --> 00:07:20,572
the followers of Mahaprabhu.

97
00:07:20,694 --> 00:07:24,004
They delight in having these discussions.

98
00:07:27,462 --> 00:07:31,462
What's the first sloka of Prema Dhama Stotram?

99
00:07:33,421 --> 00:07:34,231
Do you know?

100
00:07:34,274 --> 00:07:37,244
deva-siddha-mukta-yukta-bhakta-vrnda-vanditam

101
00:07:37,684 --> 00:07:41,714
papa-tapa-dava-daha-dagdha duhkha-khanditam

102
00:07:41,745 --> 00:07:44,585
krsna-nama-sidhu-dhama-dhanya-dana-sagaram

103
00:07:44,799 --> 00:07:47,629
prema-dhama-devam eva naumi gaura-sundaram

104
00:07:48,079 --> 00:07:49,999
Talking about Mahaprabhu.

105
00:07:53,582 --> 00:07:58,932
"The Devas, the Siddhas, the Muktas, the Yuktas, the Bhakta vrinda,

106
00:07:59,007 --> 00:08:01,497
they are all singing His praise.

107
00:08:02,418 --> 00:08:08,488
So then someone asks, you know, what is a Deva, what is a Siddha, what is a Mukta, what are Bhaktas.

108
00:08:11,411 --> 00:08:13,941
─ "Well, it's very deep!" ─ It is.

109
00:08:14,619 --> 00:08:19,139
It's, you know, endless ocean deep.

110
00:08:19,871 --> 00:08:21,941
That's what we're interested in.

111
00:08:24,716 --> 00:08:29,566
Still, we are talking to someone who knows absolutely nothing about these things.

112
00:08:29,727 --> 00:08:32,477
Why should we conceal Krishna?

113
00:08:33,628 --> 00:08:37,628
It may be the only opportunity they have in their live they hear something about Krishna.

114
00:08:39,356 --> 00:08:43,776
So, we may not want to say something so general.

115
00:08:44,819 --> 00:08:46,679
We want them to here about Krishna.

116
00:08:46,930 --> 00:08:53,500
Even if only for a moment it would be the crowning glory of their lifetime is to hear the sound of the name of Krishna.

117
00:08:53,516 --> 00:08:54,906
Once in their life.

118
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:58,960
Even you say: "Krishna says in the Bhagavad Gita:

119
00:08:59,490 --> 00:09:01,600
For the soul there is neither birth nor death."

120
00:09:01,615 --> 00:09:03,585
na jāyate mriyate vā kadācin

121
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:09,380
Maybe more then hearing the slokas, they've heard "Krishna says".

122
00:09:11,059 --> 00:09:13,389
So, it's all good.

123
00:09:17,822 --> 00:09:23,952
But we are inclined to discuss the pastimes of Sri Chaitanya Mahaprabhu.

124
00:09:25,770 --> 00:09:29,180
Especially in the association of devotees.

125
00:09:29,950 --> 00:09:35,670
If we are going to some public program and we are dealing with people have no knowledge or exposure,

126
00:09:35,689 --> 00:09:37,429
we may take another route.

127
00:09:38,945 --> 00:09:43,365
We're talking about these things all the time, a hundred times, a thousand times.

128
00:09:43,989 --> 00:09:47,169
Matchmaker.com ─ it that too deep?

129
00:09:49,273 --> 00:09:51,743
Is that something people have never heard of?

130
00:09:51,843 --> 00:09:53,123
Or can't relate to?

131
00:09:53,181 --> 00:09:57,721
If I'm talking about matchmaker.com, finding your soulmate,

132
00:09:58,760 --> 00:10:05,500
and segway from there to a little talk about God, Divinity, the Personality of Godhead.

133
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:12,710
So depends on who the audience is.

134
00:10:12,971 --> 00:10:17,371
And our audience is... we're here right now... is primarily devotees.

135
00:10:17,933 --> 00:10:23,393
And those aspiring to go deeper, to have a deeper understanding of these things.

136
00:10:23,977 --> 00:10:26,717
Which was... Our Guru Maharaj, what did he say?

137
00:10:26,921 --> 00:10:35,861
He prefers to speak on higher things in a small circle then general things, lower things in a large circle.

138
00:10:37,303 --> 00:10:39,773
That's who my Guru is.

139
00:10:41,653 --> 00:10:45,823
That's his preference. That's how he spoke.

140
00:10:47,246 --> 00:10:54,006
I'm trying to reiterate, reproduce things that I've heard from him.

141
00:10:54,832 --> 00:10:58,312
These are the things he talked about. They are very deep. That's right.

142
00:10:59,075 --> 00:10:59,995
They are.

143
00:11:00,464 --> 00:11:05,614
Swami Maharaj himself said: "He has deep realizations of Krishna. If you would have heard them, you will faint."

144
00:11:06,488 --> 00:11:09,261
That's my interest. I'm interested in those things.

145
00:11:09,761 --> 00:11:10,581
So I told ─

146
00:11:10,611 --> 00:11:17,381
when Govinda Maharaj told Guru Maharaj, he said: "Goswami Maharaj wants you to tell him something that will make him faint."

147
00:11:18,131 --> 00:11:19,471
That's my interest.

148
00:11:24,646 --> 00:11:31,286
But if someone earnestly wants to discuss other things, we are ready for that too.

149
00:11:31,999 --> 00:11:33,449
We'll discuss it again.

150
00:11:34,147 --> 00:11:46,617
I don't mean to indirectly make less of the ātmajnāna, atma-tattva, that's within the pages of Bhagavad Gita.

151
00:11:47,953 --> 00:11:51,763
I repeatedly read those slokas, relish them.

152
00:11:52,312 --> 00:11:53,712
But what is it saying there?

153
00:11:53,978 --> 00:11:56,418
āścarya-vat paśyati kaścid enam [Bg: 2.29]

154
00:11:56,538 --> 00:12:00,381
"If you have a glimpse of your soul, you'll be astonished."

155
00:12:06,316 --> 00:12:08,066
So, that's what Krishna says.

156
00:12:08,835 --> 00:12:10,525
And again, I've been this point,

157
00:12:11,967 --> 00:12:17,837
all the things He's saying there, we can repeat them with great confidence,

158
00:12:18,938 --> 00:12:21,228
considering who it is that speaking.

159
00:12:21,846 --> 00:12:23,566
So, someone's hearing that,

160
00:12:24,169 --> 00:12:26,859
it may touch them in a particular way,

161
00:12:28,504 --> 00:12:29,734
when they hear those things.

162
00:12:29,779 --> 00:12:31,639
And they want to hear more.

163
00:12:32,853 --> 00:12:35,143
To go further, to go deeper.

164
00:12:38,617 --> 00:12:42,517
But we should not forget that Krishna Consciousness ─ it's...

165
00:12:42,994 --> 00:12:45,514
there is nothing deeper then this.

166
00:12:47,250 --> 00:12:54,670
So, if in discussing it we say, from time to time, high things or deep things, that's going to happen.

167
00:12:55,426 --> 00:12:57,536
By virtue of what we're talking about.

168
00:12:57,838 --> 00:13:00,028
We are talking about the Ultimate Reality.

169
00:13:00,893 --> 00:13:03,383
And as revealed in the pastimes of Mahaprabhu.

170
00:13:04,185 --> 00:13:07,505
So it's very deep. Someone hearing those things...

171
00:13:07,537 --> 00:13:11,927
As I told, once a lady, a journalist, was interviewing me in San Jose,

172
00:13:11,943 --> 00:13:18,763
discussing many things that I didn't care to discuss. It was a very awkward conversation.

173
00:13:19,768 --> 00:13:23,318
And while I'm talking to her, Mahayogi Maharaj knocked on the door and he said:

174
00:13:23,503 --> 00:13:27,173
"There are some professors visiting from the school in the Midwest."

175
00:13:27,346 --> 00:13:32,336
I was thinking of showing them an excerpt of a video of Guru Maharaj.

176
00:13:33,202 --> 00:13:35,832
"Do you have any recommendations?" and I said:

177
00:13:35,878 --> 00:13:40,238
"Oh, show, you know, number... this one."

178
00:13:40,975 --> 00:13:41,945
And he goes: "Which one?"

179
00:13:41,971 --> 00:13:46,621
I'm saying: "The one where Mahaprabhu is saying — if I have a drop of love for Krishna, I would have died a long ago."

180
00:13:46,691 --> 00:13:53,521
He goes: "Oh, yes, yes, that's a great one." And he leaves. And he's gonna go show them this excerpt of talk of Guru Maharaj.

181
00:13:54,736 --> 00:13:59,706
And that newspaper reporter who had no interest in Krishna Consciousness other then

182
00:13:59,826 --> 00:14:06,966
finding out some, you know, ugly things or awkward things.

183
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:10,570
This is the sole purpose of this meeting.

184
00:14:11,307 --> 00:14:15,407
And I'm somehow reluctantly participating in this.

185
00:14:15,868 --> 00:14:19,948
And then, now we gonna go back to this talk and she said:

186
00:14:20,153 --> 00:14:25,363
"Can I ask you a question?" And I'm saying: "Yeah, lady, go ahead."

187
00:14:26,884 --> 00:14:33,484
And she goes: "Why did that person say 'if I had a drop of love for Krishna, I would have died a long time ago'?"

188
00:14:35,997 --> 00:14:38,147
That was interesting to her.

189
00:14:39,771 --> 00:14:42,981
Not some talk about consciousness.

190
00:14:43,174 --> 00:14:46,584
That picked her imagination.

191
00:14:47,182 --> 00:14:50,902
And I said: "Well... I'm glad you asked.

192
00:14:51,888 --> 00:14:53,848
I thought you'd never ask."

193
00:14:56,586 --> 00:15:00,096
Then I told her, as best I could, something.

194
00:15:01,945 --> 00:15:10,555
And I'm not saying: "So then we should just randomly shoot fragments of high things out into the environment."

195
00:15:11,177 --> 00:15:15,017
I'm not saying that. That's just how that happened at that time.

196
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:22,440
Yes, generally we do start with the elementary position. That's correct.

197
00:15:23,850 --> 00:15:30,330
Atma-tattva, ātmajnāna in the second chapter of Bhagavad Gita and other parts of Gita.

198
00:15:30,349 --> 00:15:33,879
And there're talks similar to that in the Bhagavatam.

199
00:15:33,919 --> 00:15:35,989
That is the way we begin.

200
00:15:37,825 --> 00:15:44,105
But there's also... you look at how Mahaprabhu teaches Rupa Goswami, rupa śikṣā, that structure.

201
00:15:44,145 --> 00:15:48,035
Wandering to the length and breath of the universe in different lifeforms,

202
00:15:48,385 --> 00:15:50,785
if they fortunate they get connection with Guru,

203
00:15:50,977 --> 00:15:53,847
and get the bhakti-lata-bija, the seed of devotion.

204
00:15:54,856 --> 00:15:58,586
That's how Mahaprabhu begins in His talk to Rupa.

205
00:15:58,850 --> 00:16:04,280
Then He talks about karmis, jnanis, yogis and devotees.

206
00:16:06,905 --> 00:16:09,105
In terms of gradation.

207
00:16:11,290 --> 00:16:14,610
Then he's talking about the seed of devotion growing and developing.

208
00:16:14,679 --> 00:16:16,819
That's for someone who is interested

209
00:16:17,515 --> 00:16:18,915
in devotion.

210
00:16:19,232 --> 00:16:22,652
Knowing about what Krishna Consciousness is.

211
00:16:24,718 --> 00:16:30,968
So, still generally we will start that way and then...

212
00:16:31,371 --> 00:16:40,571
As I told once, in a conference with reporters they ask Prabhupad, they're sitting there with their... :

213
00:16:40,605 --> 00:16:42,505
"What is the purpose of life?"

214
00:16:44,378 --> 00:16:47,068
And we were all thinking, because we're trained to say like:

215
00:16:47,091 --> 00:16:53,801
"The purpose of the human form of life is to engage in self-realization or God-realization

216
00:16:54,038 --> 00:17:02,168
or to realize your love of God." There's this wrote recitation of answers we're trained to say in general.

217
00:17:02,300 --> 00:17:05,390
So we were thinking he'll probably say one of these things.

218
00:17:05,443 --> 00:17:07,133
Wonder which one he's gonna say.

219
00:17:07,580 --> 00:17:14,950
So they go: "Swami, what is the purpose of life?" And he says: "Enjoyment."

220
00:17:17,066 --> 00:17:19,746
And they all go: "Oh, really?"

221
00:17:21,510 --> 00:17:26,040
And then he said: "Problem is, at present, no one is enjoying."

222
00:17:26,583 --> 00:17:29,223
And then he gave a little talk about that.

223
00:17:31,676 --> 00:17:33,356
About suffering.

224
00:17:35,615 --> 00:17:39,755
That's more in the theme of the second chapter of Bhagavad Gita.

225
00:17:41,077 --> 00:17:45,777
So, we worship that. And we'll forever preach that.

226
00:17:46,344 --> 00:17:55,494
But when we are with our group who except these things, embrace them,

227
00:17:55,739 --> 00:18:01,919
then we're pursuing what is exclusively Gaudiya.

228
00:18:02,560 --> 00:18:06,810
Guru Maharaj is saying: "As connotation increases, denotation decreases."

229
00:18:07,729 --> 00:18:11,629
They used to make a poster showing how everyone in the world loves Bhagavad Gita.

230
00:18:11,652 --> 00:18:12,772
Not just us.

231
00:18:13,100 --> 00:18:16,600
So, Emerson, Thoreau... Thoreau, you know:

232
00:18:16,641 --> 00:18:23,271
"In the morning I bathe my intellect in the cosmogonal and stupendous glory of the Bhagavad Gita;

233
00:18:23,295 --> 00:18:29,565
in comparison with which our modern literature seem trivial and puny."

234
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:33,626
And Nitzsche and this one, everyone loves.

235
00:18:33,649 --> 00:18:38,899
Juan Mascaro, Christopher Isherwood, Annie Besant, Hitler.

236
00:18:41,256 --> 00:18:44,016
Everybody loves the Bhagavad Gita.

237
00:18:45,265 --> 00:18:48,015
As connotation increases, denotation decreases.

238
00:18:48,049 --> 00:18:49,509
We say that we have the Gita...

239
00:18:50,365 --> 00:18:51,815
And mayavadis...

240
00:18:52,330 --> 00:18:56,700
You know, Gaudiya-vaishnavas, Sri-vaishnavas, Madhavas, Mayavadis...

241
00:18:58,659 --> 00:19:04,179
We say: "No, but Bhagavad Gita must be understood in terms of the light of Srimad Bhagavatam."

242
00:19:05,758 --> 00:19:11,178
Then not the mayavadis, others... Now it's the Vaishnavas:

243
00:19:11,501 --> 00:19:16,151
Madhava line, Sri-vaishnavas Ramanuja line, Gaudiya line.

244
00:19:16,771 --> 00:19:23,311
And if we say: "And Bhagavatam should be understood through Mahaprabhu and His, you know, Rupanuga line."

245
00:19:24,162 --> 00:19:27,682
Then you're with Gaudiya-vaishnavas.

246
00:19:31,666 --> 00:19:34,209
Still, Guru Maharaj would say —

247
00:19:34,209 --> 00:19:41,499
because, as you pointed, we do from time to time discuss things that are very high —

248
00:19:43,157 --> 00:19:48,707
"So I take the name of Nityananda — Dayal Nitai, Dayal Nitai, Dayal Nitai —

249
00:19:48,823 --> 00:19:55,763
to restore myself to my former position, 'cause maybe in discussing these high things I said something wrong,

250
00:19:58,173 --> 00:20:00,843
I made a mistake or I commited an offence.

251
00:20:01,449 --> 00:20:11,939
So I take the name of Nityananda to humbly resume my natural aspirational humble position."

